README.md

Awesome

     A curation of useful resources for learning about and using
     recursion schemes.

   Recursion schemes are simple, composable combinators, that automate the
   process of traversing and recursing through nested data structures.

Contents

     * Introductions
     * Articles
     * Papers
     * Presentations
     * Podcasts
     * Implementations

Introductions

     * [https://jtobin.io/practical-recursion-schemes]Practical Recursion
       Schemes - Introduction to pattern functors, fix points,
       anamorphisms, catamorphisms, paramorphisms and hylomorphisms,
       requiring very little prior knowledge.
     * [http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/an-introduction-to-recursion-schemes/
       ]An Introduction to Recursion Schemes - Three-part series in which
       you discover recursion schemes from scratch and implement a small
       subset of Edward Kmett's library.
     * [https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/bartosz/understanding-algebra
       s]Understanding Algebras - Bartosz Milewski explains F-algebras and
       shows how to use them in the context of catamorphisms.
     * [https://medium.com/@JosephJnk/recursion-schemes-in-javascript-and-
       flow-with-static-land-recursision-schemes-97cf10599fb7]Recursion
       Schemes in JavaScript and Flow - Series introducing recursion
       schemes and related concepts in JavaScript, aimed at developers
       with a minimal functional programming background.

Articles

     * [http://comonad.com/reader/2009/recursion-schemes/]Recursion
       Schemes: A Field Guide (Redux) - List of various recursion schemes
       with code samples.
     * [https://wiki.haskell.org/Catamorphisms]Catamorphisms - Definition
       on the Haskell Wiki.
     * [https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/edwardk/recursion-schemes/cat
       amorphisms]Catamorphisms - Short definition with code on School of
       Haskell by Edward Kmett.
     * [https://jtobin.io/rotating-squares]Rotating Squares - Using a
       hylomorphism to rotate a quadtree by Jared Tobin.
     * [https://jtobin.io/promorphisms-pre-post]Promorphisms, Pre and Post
       - Pratical examples of pre- and postpromorphisms by Jared Tobin.
     * [https://jtobin.io/time-traveling-recursion]Time Traveling
       Recursion Schemes - Exploring histo and futu by example by Jared
       Tobin.
     * [http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/recursion-schemes-part-iv-time-is-of-
       the-essence/]Recursion Schemes, Part IV: Time is of the Essence -
       Practical article about histomorphism and the futumorphism.
     * [https://github.com/sellout/recursion-scheme-talk/blob/master/cheat
       %20sheet.pdf]Cheat Sheet - Map of various recursion schemes and
       their duals.
     * [http://logji.blogspot.co.uk/2012/02/correcting-visitor-pattern.htm
       l]Correcting the Visitor pattern - Showing that the Visitor pattern
       implements an f-algebra for use with a catamorphism (in Java).

Papers

     * [http://maartenfokkinga.github.io/utwente/mmf91m.pdf]Functional
       Programming with Bananas, Lenses, Envelopes and Barbed Wire, 1991,
       Meijer et al. - The original paper most of this is based on.
     * [http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/ralf.hinze/publications/Sorting.pdf]A
       Duality of Sorts, 2013, Hinze et al. - Shows that many basic
       sorting algorithms exist as a pair, and that these pairs arise
       naturally out of the duality between folds and unfolds.
     * [http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/people/daniel.james/sorting/sorting.pdf]Sor
       ting with Bialgebras and Distributive Laws, 2012, Hinze et al. -
       Shows how paramorphisms and apomorphisms can be used for more
       efficient implementations of sorting algorithms.
     * [http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/um/people/simonpj/Papers/hmap/
       hmap.ps]Scrap your boilerplate: a practical design pattern for
       generic programming, 2003, SPJ et al. - Design pattern for writing
       programs that traverse data structures built from rich
       mutually-recursive data types.

Presentations

     * [http://www.timphilipwilliams.com/slides.html]Slidedecks by Tim
       Philip Williams - "Recursion Schemes by Example" and "Exotic Tools
       for Exotic Trades" provide concise definitions as well as practical
       examples of many recursion schemes.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9EGYSb9vov8]Unifying Structured
       Recursion Schemes - 12 min presentation by Ralf Hinze, Nicolas Wu,
       and Jeremy Gibbons.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zw9KeP3OzpU]Recursion Schemes -
       Presented by Tim Williams at the London Haskell meetup.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PK4SOaAGVfg]F-algebras or: How I
       Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Type System - Presented by
       Anthony Burzillo at the NYC Haskell User's Group.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i5A2Amfcir8]A Gentle Introduction
       to Recursion Schemes - Presented by Jean Remi Desjardins at
       Lambdaconf 2016.
     * [https://github.com/sellout/recursion-scheme-talk]recursion-scheme-
       talk - Collection of slide decks about recursion schemes.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Kr7IykGMzU]Bracer: Transforming
       Real-World Languages with Coproducts and Recursion Schemes -
       High-level talk about structuring programs with coproducts and
       recursion schemes by Patrick Thomson.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=24UoRaoKLjM]Recursion: Where
       Functional Programming Hits Bottom - Introduction to recursive fix
       point data structures and recursion schemes in Haskell and Scala by
       Greg Pfeil.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-98fR9VmLbQ]Programming with
       algebras - Bartosz Milewski's article in talk form, presented at
       LambdaCon.

Podcasts

     * [http://www.magicreadalong.com/]Magic Read Along - Casual
       discussions about category theory that often bring up recursion
       schemes, including
       [http://www.magicreadalong.com/episode/33]episode 33 which talks
       about Histomorphisms and Futumorphisms.

Implementations

     * [https://github.com/ekmett/recursion-schemes/]recursion-schemes for
       Haskell - The canonical implementation by Edward Kmett.
     * [https://github.com/slamdata/matryoshka]Matryoshka for Scala -
       Generalized folds, unfolds, and traversals for fixed point data
       structures.
     * [https://github.com/vmchale/recursion_schemes/]recursion_schemes
       for Idris, based off Edward Kmett's Haskell library.
     * [https://github.com/slamdata/purescript-matryoshka]purescript-matry
       oshka for PureScript - Work-in-process port of matryoshka.
     * [https://github.com/JosephJNK/static-land-recursion-schemes]static-
       land-recursion-schemes for JavaScript/Flow - Schemes for data
       structures written in the style of
       [https://github.com/gcanti/flow-static-land]flow-static-land.
     * [https://github.com/kategory/kategory/tree/master/kategory-recursio
       n]Kategory-recursion for Kotlin - a re-envisioning based off
       Matryoshka using lightweight higher kinded polymorphism.

